<dl id="n01100a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01100a">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01100a"> 100(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pointers (stars show polestar)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[PHOTOGRAPHING SHOOTING STARS. By Dr. W. J. S. LOCKYER. / Director of the Norman Lockyer Observatory]</font> The <mark>Pole Star</mark> can easily be found as it is situated due north and lies on the prolongation of a line joining the <mark>two bright stars known as &ldquo;the pointers,&rdquo;</mark> in the constellation of the Great Bear or Plough. <small> <a name="DM10jan23" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DM10jan23"><cite title="source">Daily Mail</cite></a> (10 January 1923) 6/4</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05156j" href="c05all.htm#c05156j">VI.C.05:156(j)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
